[31m-## Sharing your solution[m
[31m-[m
[31m-There are multiple places you can share your solution:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-1. Share your solution page in the **#finished-projects** channel of the [Slack community](https://www.frontendmentor.io/slack). [m
[31m-2. Tweet [@frontendmentor](https://twitter.com/frontendmentor) and mention **@frontendmentor**, including the repo and live URLs in the tweet. We'd love to take a look at what you've built and help share it around.[m
[31m-3. Share your solution on other social channels like LinkedIn.[m
[31m-4. Blog about your experience building your project. Writing about your workflow, technical choices, and talking through your code is a brilliant way to reinforce what you've learned. Great platforms to write on are [dev.to](https://dev.to/), [Hashnode](https://hashnode.com/), and [CodeNewbie](https://community.codenewbie.org/).[m
[31m-[m
[31m-We provide templates to help you share your solution once you've submitted it on the platform. Please do edit them and include specific questions when you're looking for feedback. [m
[31m-[m
[31m-The more specific you are with your questions the more likely it is that another member of the community will give you feedback.[m
